- Determinant calculation
- Minor matrix extraction
- Matrix inverse calculation
- Matrix multiplication
- Matrix transposition

The main `transform` function wraps everything together and handles error cases appropriately. The implementation is numerically stable for most practical cases, though for very large matrices or ill-conditioned matrices, numerical precision issues might arise.

