The Try monad represents computations that might fail. Instead of using traditional try-catch blocks, which can lead to imperative and harder-to-compose code, Try provides a functional approach to error handling. Originally popularized in Scala, Try wraps a value that either contains a successful result or an error, allowing developers to chain operations and handle errors in a consistent way.

