These are several examples of prompt optimization functions that I have written in typescript. I want to make sure that the expose a similar api interface that will make them consistent in use and easy to switch one for the other. 

For example
```
export function tot(model: LanguageModel, initialThought: string) {
  const instance = new TreeOfThought({ model, initialThought });
  return instance.findBestSolution();
}
```
is the function TreeOfThought. It accepts a LanguageModel and string that serves as the initial prompt. Some of the other implementations require more than this, but hopefully those are optional and have sane defaults. 

What I want you to do is look at this entire bit of code and suggest ways that each of these implementations can be updated to create a cohesive and consistent api for all of these optimization functions.

